msgstr "Control de los Estados"

#: ../workflow/introduction.rst:51
msgid "What transitions are available **out**"
msgstr "¿Qué transiciones están disponibles **fuera**?"

#: ../workflow/introduction.rst:52
msgid "What ``permissions`` are assigned to which ``roles`` *locally* to the object"
msgstr "¿Qué ``permisos`` se asignan a qué ``roles`` *localmente* al objeto?"

#: ../workflow/introduction.rst:53
msgid "What ``groups`` are assigned to which ``roles`` *locally* to the object"
msgstr "¿Qué ``grupos`` se asignan a qué ``roles`` *localmente* al objeto?"

#: ../workflow/introduction.rst:55
msgid "This is probably the least-used aspect of workflow"
msgstr "Este es probablemente el aspecto menos utilizado del flujo de trabajo"

#: ../workflow/introduction.rst:56
msgid "It can be spectacularly useful"
msgstr "Puede ser espectacularmente útil"

#: ../workflow/introduction.rst:59
msgid "Transitions Control"
msgstr "Control de transiciones"

#: ../workflow/introduction.rst:61
msgid "What ``state`` they will end in"
msgstr "¿En qué \"estado\" terminarán?"

#: ../workflow/introduction.rst:62
msgid "What conditions or ``gaurds`` are required for the transition to be available"
msgstr ""
"¿Qué condiciones o ``garantías`` se requieren para que la transición esté disponible?"

#: ../workflow/introduction.rst:64
msgid ""
"These can be ``permissions`` of the user, ``roles`` a user has, ``groups`` to which the "
"user belongs, or even the boolean value of *'TALES*' expressions"
msgstr ""
"Estos pueden ser ``permisos`` del usuario, ``roles`` que tiene un usuario, ``grupos`` a "
"los que pertenece el usuario, o incluso el valor booleano de las expresiones *'TALES*'"

#: ../workflow/introduction.rst:66
msgid ""
"What ``scripts`` will be executed before and after the transition occurs (again, not "
